@node AG-12 "EPI-SIM Documentation: History"
 V 1.2 (September 1995): First public version 
                         -full of bugs concerning font sensitivity
 V 1.5 (March 1996):     -Epi-Sim now opens its own screen (I have given
                          up writing a font sensitive program)
                         -some corrections in the graphics
                         -@{"Repro-time" link AG-8} added
                         -bigger field
                         -rewriting of critical parts and usement
                          of registers make the program faster
                          (especially in NOANIM mode)
 V 1.6 (September 1996): -Fixed number at beginning bug (you could never start with 0 indies)
                         -made field density an enabled/disabled option
                         -now can configure reproduction type:@{"Smooth repro " link AG-6}
                         -save config option enabled
                         -some minor fixes I can`t remember

             If no more bugs occur this will be the last version.
             
@endnode 


@node AG-20 "EPI-SIM Documentation: Fields"

The program simulates graphically the movement of
solids with mass or charge in electric magnetic
or gravity-fields.

Feature list:
-Set of up to 20 fixed solids(mass and charge configurable) 
 on the sim screen
-Set of magnetic fields
-Set of moving solids that are accelerated by the forces of
 the fixed solids and the B field.
-Set of barricades which avoids movement of moving solids
 over special points
-Graph that shows a(t) and v(t)
-Plot of F vectors
-saving and loading of field configurations
-5 example fields included 
-Documemtation contains an easy explanation of the theoretical
 and a less easy one of the technical backgrounds.

@endnode 
